The paper deals with energy efficiency in the presence of channel uncertainty and queueing constraints, which are topics typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of MMSE estimation and effective capacity formulation suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of power allocation and tradeoffs suggests a possible connection to game theory (cs.GT).
